#. VAR: rāgādipeyyālaṃ (bj) | paṇṇāsakāsaṅgahitā suttantā (s1-3)
msgctxt "an4.274:0.2"
msgid "28. Rāgapeyyāla "
msgstr "28. Abbreviated Texts Beginning with Greed "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: catusatipaṭṭhānasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an4.274:0.3"
msgid "274. Satipaṭṭhānasutta "
msgstr "274. Mindfulness Meditation "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an4.274:1.1"
msgid "“Rāgassa, bhikkhave, abhiññāya cattāro dhammā bhāvetabbā. "
msgstr "“For insight into greed, four things should be developed. "

msgctxt "an4.274:1.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro? "
msgstr "What four? "

msgctxt "an4.274:1.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ; "
msgstr "Firstly, a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

msgctxt "an4.274:1.4"
msgid "vedanāsu … pe … citte … pe … dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ. "
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of feelings … mind … principles—keen, aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world. "

msgctxt "an4.274:1.5"
msgid "Rāgassa, bhikkhave, abhiññāya ime cattāro dhammā bhāvetabbā”ti. "
msgstr "For insight into greed, these four things should be developed.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.274:1.6"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

